result.execSummary:
The defendant Travis Brookes Enders was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting/Failing to Stop/Fleeing, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(2t).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Shall receive 1 day presentence credit should supervision be revoked

miscConds.notes: All Financial obligations shall be paid to the Clerk of Courts within 60 days unless a payment plan is established.

Defendant shall not consume alcohol or other intoxicants.  Defendant must maintain absolute sobriety and shall not go upon the premises of any establishment whose primary business activity involves the sale or distribution of alcoholic beverages, including bars, taverns, liquor stores and beer tents. AMENDED 2/10/17 - MAY GO ON THE PREMISES OF BARS AND TAVERNS FOR THE PURPOSE OF CONDUCTING BUSINESS ONLY AND SHOULD NOT CONSUME ANY INTOXICANTS WHILE ON THE PREMISES OF THOSE ESTABLISHMENTS.

timeConds.notes: Sentence shall commence on or before Court ordered start date; with work release and transfer privileges
